				&quot;we dont want mage to be solely &quot;mana-factories&quot;<BR>
<BR>
I think this is the essence of what VI had in mind when the destoryed &quot;mod-rods&quot;. What i think VI didnt take into account is that mages are NOT simple &quot;mana-factories&quot; in everyday xp groups or soloing. mages are indeed great dmg dealers in xp groups. Raids change everything. Point in case. Shamans in theory a lvl 60 sham can solo dragons in WW, so appearently shams can put out alot of dmg. BUT during a raid what is a shams job? Buff/Malo/Turgurs/Cripple/Spot Heal....see any dmg in there? the occasionally epic landing on a 500,000+ mob hardly counts. Druids ?? buffs/spot heals some nuking, Chanters? Buffs/Sieve. The point being on raids everyone jobs changes to fit the needs of the raid. Are mage soley mana/factories?? NO, they are indeed mana factories on raids, but raids are not the whole of who a mage is......Wake up VI and fix what you broke, before i am forced to seek out other addictions
