				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				 Anyone got 2750 mana to spare?<BR>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>
 Rod of &quot;mystical mass transvestite urges&quot; cost 2750 mana to cast. Now I understand that is gives out a lot of rods at once and thats nice.. the rods do have the downside of only being able to be used every 5 minutes. <BR>
<BR>
The big downside to me is that by not being obsessed with getting all int and only int items I have find myself with 225 int. At level 58, 225 int (plus the many +mana items I am wearing) dont add up to 2750 mana, so at level 58 I cannot cast a level 56 spell.<BR>
<BR>
I always had fun trying to use my mana very efficiently and cutting corners where I could. Its fun and I like having a variety of equipment that boost some other stats to (agility is nice, and sta is cool too since dying sucks). Now it seems I have one option if I want to contunue to play my mage and use the spells I have.. to let verant lead me by the nose and get the gear &quot;they&quot; think I should wear so I can cast a spell ONCE and blow all my mana out the window (and I think Ill start kicking puppies if I am ever able to cast it and I fizzle once).<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
To those of you who do have enough mana to cast the spell my hat is off to you (oops there goes some int points).<BR>
<BR>
The spell they added so we could have a single target T-rod spell appears to be missing in action.. no one know where it is .. and verant even said it was in the Bazaar. I feel used .. I have very little motivation to play the game.. gee maybe if I power level for 2 days straight and quit my job Ill hit level 59 and then maybe i can cast my level 56 spell. 
				</font>
			</td>

